Jim Norton - Trinkets I Own Made From Gorilla Hands

Jim Norton (born July 19, 1968) is an American stand-up comedian, actor and author hailing from New Jersey. He is heard on the nationally syndicated Opie and Anthony radio program. He has appeared on the Tonight Show with Jay Leno five times and the Late Show with David Letterman, filmed an HBO stand-up special for the series One Night Stand, co-starred in the short-lived HBO sitcom Lucky Louie and had a cameo in the film Spider-Man. He is best known for his so-called &quot;cringe humor&quot; style, which deals with sensitive and uncomfortable subjects. Norton recently hosted the filming of four episodes for an HBO stand-up showcase titled Down and Dirty with Jim Norton.
